COMPONENT NAME: IKM SQL Control Append (SOA XREF)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description : - Integrates data in any ISO-92 compliant database target table in truncate / insert (append) mode. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled. - When loading data to the target, this KM also populates PK/GUID XRef table on a separate database - As of 11.1.2.10, this IKM supports new XREF data structure such as
ROW_ID VARCHAR2(48) NOT NULL PK, APP1 VARCHAR2(100), APP2 VARCHAR2(100), ... COM VARCHAR2(100), LAST_MODIFIED TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
in addition to the original, fixed XREF data structure such as
XREF_TABLE_NAME NOT NULL VARCHAR2(2000) XREF_COLUMN_NAME NOT NULL VARCHAR2(2000) ROW_NUMBER NOT NULL VARCHAR2(48) VALUE NOT NULL VARCHAR2(2000) IS_DELETED NOT NULL VARCHAR2(1) LAST_MODIFIED NOT NULL TIMESTAMP(6)
Please note that one can only individually name each new XREF data table, while for an roiginal XREF data table it is harded-coded to XREF_DATA.
Important restrictions for XREF usage:
This IKM : - assumes that it is used in conjunction with the LKM SQL to SQL (SOA XREF) or LKM MSSQL to SQL (SOA XREF) - uses a hard coded logical schema XREF that points to the Oracle instance that holds the XREF_DATA table - You have to create this schema in your Oracle topology
For legacy XREF_DATA table usage only: USE UD1 to mark columns you want to populate with the COMMON ID calculated from XREF. A mapping must exists on this column, use a constatnt expression like 'X', otherwise the flag UD1 will not be saved.
Other standard restrictions: - When working with journalized data, if the "Synchronize deletions from journal" is executed, the deleted rows on the target are committed regardless of the COMMIT option - The TRUNCATE option is not implemented on all RDBMs - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - When using the RECYCLE_ERRORS option, you have to set an Update Key for your interface. - When using this module with a journalized source table, data are automatically filtered to not include source deletions. - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Commit all data inserted in the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected by flow control in a previous execution of this interface.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

MANDATORY:
Enter 'New' to use new XREF_DATA Table structure -
ROW_ID VARCHAR2(48) NOT NULL PK, APP1 VARCHAR2(100), APP2 VARCHAR2(100), ... COM VARCHAR2(100), LAST_MODIFIED TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
Otherwise enter 'Legacy' to use legacy XREF_DATA Table -
XREF_TABLE_NAME NOT NULL VARCHAR2(2000) XREF_COLUMN_NAME NOT NULL VARCHAR2(2000) ROW_NUMBER NOT NULL VARCHAR2(48) VALUE NOT NULL VARCHAR2(2000) IS_DELETED NOT NULL VARCHAR2(1) LAST_MODIFIED NOT NULL TIMESTAMP(6)
MANDATORY: Table to store cross-reference information. Default to XREF_DATA.
(For New XREF data structure) MANDATORY: specify which column of a XREF data table to store key values.
Expression to populate the row num.
MANDATORY: Enter the expression used to populate the row_number for the XREF table. Valid examples are: for Oracle :SYS_GUID() ,MY_SEQUENCE.NEXTVAL etc..
Table Name to use in the XREF table
(Legacy XREF only) MANDATORY: Table Name to use in the XREF table. Example: ORDERS
(Legacy XREF only) MANDATORY: Primary key column name to use as a literal in the XREF table

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%>, SYSGUID, SKEY_VAL ) select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",\n\t", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%>, <%=odiRef.getOption("XREF_SYS_GUID_EXPRESSION")%>, SKEY_VAL from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%> where <% if (odiRef.getPop("HAS_JRN").equals("0")) { %> (1=1) <%} else {%> JRN_FLAG <> 'D' <% } %> <%=odiRef.getJoin()%> <%=odiRef.getFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=odiRef.getHaving()%>

<%if ( odiRef.getOption("FLOW_CONTROL").equals("1") ) { %> insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW")%> ) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> T where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK")%> ) and E.ODI_ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ODI_ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>' <% } %>
Drop remote PK Table on XREF DB
Create remote PK Table on XREF DB
Load PKs and GUIDS to remote PK tab
select SKEY_VAL PK_VAL, SYSGUID GUID_VAL from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%>
Assign new rownums to non-exist. PK

/* This step applies all mappings to the target table */ /* Columns marked as UD1 are populated using the calculated COMMON_ID retrieved from the XREF table */ insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW and not UD1 and not TRG")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW and not UD1 and TRG")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[COL_NAME] /* COMMON ID */", ",
	", "", "UD1")%> ) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW and not UD1 and not TRG")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", "", "INS and REW and not UD1 and TRG")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "SYSGUID", ",
	", "", "UD1")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
Drop remote PK Table on XREF DB
Update remote PK with existing GUID

<%if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_METHOD"))){%> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
